1
00:00:01,921 --> 00:00:31,658
Namo tassa bhagavato arahato samma sambodassam Namo tassa bhagavato arahato samma sambodassam Namo tassa bhagavato arahato samma sambodassam Homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble and fully self-awakened one.

2
00:00:33,106 --> 00:00:51,008
So I thought today, being the new year and everybody's made these amazing new year resolutions, that we would do the four bases of power, or better still, better translation, the four bases that lead to success.

3
00:00:52,149 --> 00:00:57,155
Now these are part of the 37 requisites for awakening.

4
00:00:57,322 --> 00:01:24,948
the bodhi paki adama and this is the practice that the buddha teaches us so it begins with the four foundations of mindfulness and then you have the four right efforts i won't go into details it takes too long then you get these four roads to success or bases for success then you have the spiritual faculties and when you achieve stream entrant they become the five spiritual powers

5
00:01:25,519 --> 00:01:32,853
Then you have the seven factors of awakening, the Noble Eightfold Path, and all that adds up to 37.

6
00:01:33,975 --> 00:01:47,882
And according to Bhikkhu Thanissaro, Ajahn Thanissaro, some of you will know his very good work, he reckons that this relates to the 37 chords

7
00:01:48,503 --> 00:02:18,307
of those times if you wanted to play the vina which was like a guitar then you had to be able to find these 37 chords i don't know i've never seen proof of that but there we are so the nice connection there between music and the buddha dhamma anyway when you practice these four bases you get what's known as the iddys or the powers uh in the uh you might have heard them call the siddhis

8
00:02:19,468 --> 00:02:45,072
So you can bi-locate, you can appear in two different places or more, you can fly through the air and through walls, you can have the divine eye where you see beyond what's possible through the physical body, and the same with the divine ear, you can hear things which you can't hear if the mind is constrained by the physical body.

9
00:02:45,187 --> 00:02:46,969
You can read other people's minds.

10
00:02:47,229 --> 00:02:52,097
You can see how people are born and die depending on their karma.

11
00:02:52,236 --> 00:02:53,359
So these are just some of them.

12
00:02:53,979 --> 00:02:56,903
Now, all these are very wonderful and magical.

13
00:02:57,544 --> 00:03:06,377
But the really important one for us is that it leads to the destruction of the mental defilements.

14
00:03:07,199 --> 00:03:09,421
So that's where they become important for us.

15
00:03:10,026 --> 00:03:16,736
So these four bases or four qualities are what we need in order to purify the heart.

16
00:03:17,277 --> 00:03:21,805
And that's an absolute necessity in order to become fully liberated.

17
00:03:24,027 --> 00:03:26,651
Okay, so what are these four bases?

18
00:03:27,610 --> 00:03:31,818
The first one is chanda, and it translates as desire.

19
00:03:31,897 --> 00:03:36,686
Now, in the dependent origination, of course, we have this word tanha.

20
00:03:36,705 --> 00:03:39,290
That's always an unwholesome desire.

21
00:03:39,311 --> 00:03:44,180
It's always a desire which is driven by greed, hatred or delusion.

22
00:03:44,941 --> 00:03:51,592
Chanda can be unskillful, but here, of course, it's skillful.

23
00:03:51,724 --> 00:04:06,443
uh wish now it's not just a wish it's an aspiration it's a longing it's a yearning for something right so there's it's in order to get this liberation from suffering you've got to really want it okay

24
00:04:08,431 --> 00:04:24,262
Now, once you've got that desire, once you've got that aspiration, the next thing that arises to support that, of course, is your energy, your commitment, true grit, you know, doggedness, perseverance and all that drive.

25
00:04:26,216 --> 00:04:32,045
And then with that, there comes a devotion to it.

26
00:04:32,446 --> 00:04:33,687
So that word is citta.

27
00:04:33,767 --> 00:04:38,153
Now citta refers to both the heart and the mind.

28
00:04:38,274 --> 00:04:41,137
In other words, it's the whole mental process.

29
00:04:42,259 --> 00:04:47,266
And it demands a complete devotion from the heart to the task in hand.

30
00:04:47,326 --> 00:04:51,312
It's to do with attitude, dedication, devotion, care.

31
00:04:51,985 --> 00:04:58,360
And this is where the Buddha's word appamado, one of his favorite words, which means diligence.

32
00:04:58,440 --> 00:05:05,437
It's one of his last two words, appamado sampadita, you know, really strive, really work for your liberation.

33
00:05:06,041 --> 00:05:07,783
So there's the citta.

34
00:05:08,464 --> 00:05:24,666
And then finally, there's this word vimamsa, which translates as discrimination, reflection, knowing what you're doing, constantly reflecting on how you feel, what you're doing, what the process is, where you're going, etc.

35
00:05:25,988 --> 00:05:31,475
So these four qualities, I'm sure all of you have exercised these.

36
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:39,372
They are necessary for spiritual attainment, but they're necessary for anything that you set about in ordinary daily life.

37
00:05:40,192 --> 00:05:50,494
If you set yourself a goal, whatever it is, even if it's a simple thing like having to replant the garden or a job of work,

38
00:05:50,473 --> 00:06:00,872
You know, you've got to have these qualities and if one of them is missing or if one of them is not up to standard, then it undermines the project.

39
00:06:00,932 --> 00:06:03,797
It'll undermine your process.

40
00:06:06,300 --> 00:06:08,365
Let's see now.

41
00:06:09,307 --> 00:06:11,550
I'm just thinking of my own personal.

42
00:06:11,591 --> 00:06:16,259
There's about four or five times in my life where I've had to put some special effort in.

43
00:06:17,319 --> 00:06:18,903
One of them was when I was a student.

44
00:06:19,644 --> 00:06:22,468
So I just lived the good old student life.

45
00:06:22,870 --> 00:06:27,838
And I was doing at the time this combination of a BA with a teacher's certificate.

46
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:35,055
And in that very same year, they'd actually instituted the Bachelor of Education, which would have been far easier.

47
00:06:35,115 --> 00:06:41,711
Anyway, by the time I got to the fourth year, I knew I actually knew nothing.

48
00:06:41,831 --> 00:06:44,577
I had to pull my socks up, as they say.

49
00:06:44,677 --> 00:06:53,769
And I really, really, really wanted that BA because it's a passport to jobs and all sorts of stuff, especially in teaching.

50
00:06:54,589 --> 00:06:56,812
So I really had to put my heart and soul into it.

51
00:06:56,874 --> 00:07:01,740
And I remember working 12, 14 hours a day trying to get this stuff into my head.

52
00:07:03,461 --> 00:07:04,684
But what was missing there?

53
00:07:04,803 --> 00:07:07,307
So I had the desire, I had the aspiration.

54
00:07:07,408 --> 00:07:09,189
I really, really wanted that BA.

55
00:07:09,810 --> 00:07:12,033
I had the energy because I was young anyway.

56
00:07:12,165 --> 00:07:14,870
I had the energy, the empowerment to do it.

57
00:07:15,430 --> 00:07:17,694
My heart was completely devoted to it.

58
00:07:18,036 --> 00:07:20,879
But I'm also sure about the discrimination and reflection.

59
00:07:21,500 --> 00:07:26,370
So in those days, I don't remember anybody teaching you study skills or anything like that.

60
00:07:26,470 --> 00:07:30,276
You just sort of hung on in there and drove it in.

61
00:07:30,728 --> 00:07:36,620
If I'd have had some sort of guidance on study skills, it probably would have been that much easier for me.

62
00:07:37,221 --> 00:07:44,898
So I wasn't really reflecting on the way that I was studying or the way that I had chosen to do this work.

63
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:49,968
And it probably led to inefficiencies and all sorts of stuff.

64
00:07:50,843 --> 00:08:00,622
So I think if you look back into your life, I think you'll find there were times when you really had to put your body and soul into something, right?

65
00:08:00,942 --> 00:08:05,110
I use soul, of course, in a Buddhist sense.

66
00:08:06,793 --> 00:08:08,177
So here we have...

67
00:08:09,052 --> 00:08:10,935
Here we have these four qualities.

68
00:08:11,915 --> 00:08:16,483
You have to have an aspiration, a yearning, a real zeal for something.

69
00:08:16,942 --> 00:08:21,610
And there has to come that energy, which includes a sort of diligence.

70
00:08:22,230 --> 00:08:24,394
Your heart has to be right behind it.

71
00:08:24,834 --> 00:08:27,177
And there's this constant reflection.

72
00:08:27,242 --> 00:08:51,124
so in our spiritual life every day you see there's that if every time you wake up in the morning to set yourself to make this a day of mindfulness affectionate mindfulness i mean that's what the buddha wants us to do that's his teaching in the better sutta the discourse on goodwill

73
00:08:51,104 --> 00:08:58,176
to develop not just a mindfulness, but something that's coming up, something that engages also the heart.

74
00:08:58,756 --> 00:09:01,179
And that's your sense of care.

75
00:09:01,740 --> 00:09:03,443
So it's care and attention.

76
00:09:03,664 --> 00:09:08,251
Care and attention leads to this affectionate mindfulness.

77
00:09:09,024 --> 00:09:13,970
And sometimes you have to give yourself a really good aspiration.

78
00:09:14,049 --> 00:09:22,577
So the aspiration, whatever it is, the end of suffering, make life a bit easier, movement towards contentment, it's better for other people.

79
00:09:24,019 --> 00:09:26,902
You can always bring others in.

80
00:09:27,403 --> 00:09:34,490
And then to raise that energy, the commitment to your practice, and then this constant reflection.

81
00:09:35,129 --> 00:09:37,732
So throughout the day when the mind's wandering,

82
00:09:37,982 --> 00:09:40,586
You find yourself all over the place just to stop for a minute.

83
00:09:40,605 --> 00:09:41,605
Whoa, where am I going?

84
00:09:41,647 --> 00:09:42,447
What am I doing?

85
00:09:42,486 --> 00:09:47,471
And in that way, we're slowly developing these qualities, right?

86
00:09:47,491 --> 00:09:50,075
And well, that's the path.

87
00:09:50,134 --> 00:09:52,756
I mean, it's pretty straightforward, really, once you're into it.

88
00:09:54,458 --> 00:09:57,100
So that's what I've got for this evening.

89
00:09:57,341 --> 00:10:00,485
And it supports whatever resolutions you've made.

90
00:10:01,225 --> 00:10:04,969
So a resolution normally lasts for as long as you say it, right?

91
00:10:06,197 --> 00:10:12,572
So it's no good saying, oh, you know, I won't eat, I won't have any tea from now on.

92
00:10:12,995 --> 00:10:15,200
It'll last about 10 minutes, right?

93
00:10:15,220 --> 00:10:21,595
So you've got to keep reinforcing that commitment, whatever your resolution has been.

94
00:10:21,634 --> 00:10:24,341
Okay.

95
00:10:26,144 --> 00:10:26,585
Very good.

96
00:10:26,684 --> 00:10:27,326
Short and sweet.

97
00:10:27,866 --> 00:10:43,274
I hope these words have been of some assistance that I have not caused confusion and that by your devotion to the practice and the four bases of success, you will be liberated from all suffering sooner rather than later.

